The Colbert Report 2014 04 30 Audra McDonald WEB-DL 720p

Audra McDonald is a singer and actress currently starring as Billie Holiday in the Broadway musical "Lady Day at Emerson's Bar & Grill." She is one of three people in Tony history to have won five awards; these were for her roles in "Porgy and Bess" (2012), "A Raisin in the Sun" (2004), "Ragtime" (1998), "Master Class" (1996) and "Carousel" (1994). She has also won Grammy Awards for Best Opera Recording and Best Classical Album. On television, McDonald performed as Mother Abbess in NBC's live musical version of "The Sound of Music" (2013) and played Naomi Bennett on ABC's "Private Practice."
